<p>I have some problems rendering dropdown menu with Ember.js and HtmlBars. Data I have for menu is in array, something like this:</p>  <pre><code>[{name: 'A', lvl: 0}, {name: 'B', lvl: 1}, {name: 'C', lvl: 0}, {name: 'D', lvl: 1}, , {name: 'E', lvl: 1}] </code></pre>  <p>which should result in following html</p>  <pre><code>&lt;ul&gt;   &lt;li&gt; &lt;a&gt; A &lt;/a&gt;      &lt;ul&gt;       &lt;li&gt; &lt;a&gt; B &lt;/a&gt; &lt;/li&gt;     &lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt; &lt;a&gt; C &lt;/a&gt;      &lt;ul&gt;       &lt;li&gt; &lt;a&gt; D &lt;/a&gt; &lt;/li&gt;       &lt;li&gt; &lt;a&gt; E &lt;/a&gt; &lt;/li&gt;     &lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; </code></pre>  <p>and it would have following structure(with css it will become nice dropdown)</p>  <ul> <li>A  <ul> <li>B</li> </ul></li> <li>C  <ul> <li>D</li> <li>E</li> </ul></li> </ul>  <p>The problem is that HTMLbars does not allow following structures</p>  <pre><code>{{#if (condition1)}}   &lt;ul class="d-menu" data-role="dropdown"&gt; {{/if}}  {{#if (condition2)}}   &lt;/ul&gt; {{/if}} </code></pre>  <p>Now, I am aware that this is not a bug, but project decision, but I am unsure how to overcome that limitation and to do what I need? The only option I currently see is to generate html string in js code, as I am not allowed to change data model format. If it is possible to replace HTMLbars with something different, it would be acceptable solution for me.</p>